<DED>OUTPUT_FORMAT = 'pretty'


def _repr_unicode(dumper, data):
    <IND>"""Fix yaml str representation."""
    ascii_data = data.encode('ascii', 'ignore')
    if '\n' in data:
        <IND>return dumper.represent_scalar(u'tag:yaml.org,2002:str', ascii_data,
                                       style='|')
    <DED>else:
        <IND>return dumper.represent_scalar(u'tag:yaml.org,2002:str', ascii_data)


<DED><DED>def _repr_tuple(dumper, data):
    <IND>"""Fix yaml tuple representation (use list)."""
    return dumper.represent_list(list(data))


<DED>def _repr_none(dumper, data_unused):
    <IND>"""Fix yaml None representation (use ~)."""
    return dumper.represent_scalar(u'tag:yaml.org,2002:null', '~')


# This will be invoked on module import once.
<DED>yaml.add_representer(unicode, _repr_unicode)
yaml.add_representer(str, _repr_unicode)
yaml.add_representer(tuple, _repr_tuple)
yaml.add_representer(type(None), _repr_none)


def _dump_yaml(obj):
    <IND>"""Returns yaml representation of the object."""
    return yaml.dump(obj,
                     default_flow_style=False,
                     explicit_start=True,
                     explicit_end=True)
